        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 9:57AM EDT by NWS Tallahassee FL</headline>
        <description>At 957 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Madison, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Madison, Lake Park, Valdosta, I-75 At Exit 16, Remerton, Dasher, Twin
Lakes, Cherry Lake, Hamburg, Pinetta, Valdosta Regional Airport,
Kinderlou, I-75 At Exit 5, Nankin, Clyattville, Hanson, I-75 At Exit
22, and I-75 At Exit 11.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
